s="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="N_r(\mathcal W)"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base" style="margin-right: -0.085em;"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.085em;">N</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">r</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">(</span></span> <span class="mjx-texatom"><span class="mjx-mrow"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-cal-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.372em; padding-right: 0.046em;">W</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>将随模型维度<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="d"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.003em;">d</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>呈指数缩放，因此生成的边界不会变得比 VC 更紧。然而，从概念上讲，这越来越接近模型子类复杂性的想法。不同之处在于，覆盖数字仍然将每个子类视为相同，并且我们还没有以任何原则性的方式进行粗粒度处理。</p><h2>单一模型复杂性</h2><p>研究单个模型的复杂性比限制整个模型类要容易得多。单模型复杂性的大多数概念都基于复杂性作为对噪声敏感性的概念：应用于输入的噪声（<strong>裕度理论</strong>）、应用于权重的噪声（<strong>最小锐度/平坦度</strong>）以及应用于训练样本的噪声（<strong>算法）稳定性和鲁棒性</strong>）。</p><h3>边距</h3><p>边际理论研究同名<i>边际</i>，即样本到分类器决策边界的最小距离。余量越大，分类器对输入数据中的小扰动就越鲁棒，因此我们期望它更好地推广到新数据。 </p><figure class="image"><img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/k7vju08ta9rb5drwbtrj" srcset="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/wqq5t1f0wsxwxbllc66m 144w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/qnoh9nhyzgvhyyx2hmll 224w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/hccrthd6th8x9vx3ffro 304w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/z6t7vq2m4eqw4uqblvtw 384w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/xu9xwfkpazsiaggexfqs 464w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/yjyo2qdpclcoiiig5kuf 544w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/l2j47l3vbuu673wqanu7 624w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/fkjvwsuyo2utghh9mlm9 704w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/u6xxooiucqb1fyonu4vi 784w"><figcaption>较大的余量，即距决策边界的最小距离，意味着对噪声的鲁棒性更强。</figcaption></figure><p>这可以追溯到支持向量机 (SVM) 的美好时光，您可以显式计算边距并使用它们来设计更强大的分类器（请参阅<a href="https://link.springer.com/book/10.1007/978-1-4757-3264-1">Vapnik (1995)</a> ）。对于 DNN，计算边距是很棘手的。</p><p>更根本的问题是“大利润=更好的泛化”这一假设并不适用于现实模型。您认为以下两个决策边界中哪一个更能概括？ </p><figure class="image"><img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/jhgf7ckyzxzyw4px8yvu" srcset="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/zlj0riaqinszrq0bj3im 144w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/dugmhv6kyzscxa1dmpbx 224w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/fxndaudycb28cv1xnthq 304w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/tmgvd7hzullv3labdnzl 384w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/wiep5iztyqqj9ojo1vnr 464w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/v0obxv9kzglghwsyzowm 544w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/kwirsieon4nsh4iextbh 624w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/negy1kb2fy6dn61fw9ak 704w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/h3qosjwuc3wicmb6ilmw 784w"><figcaption>随着决策边界复杂性的增加，泛化和边际最大化之间的联系并不像边际理论所假设的那样是不言自明的。</figcaption></figure><p>边际理论似乎确实具有一定的解释力，特别是在数据更简单、更结构化的情况下（例如， <a href="https://openreview.net/forum?id=QPMfCLnIqf">Mohamadi 等人，2023</a> ）。研究输入噪声敏感性的基本想法仍然是一个很好的想法。只是对利润率的具体关注似乎被过分强调了。</p><h3>最小平整度/锐度</h3><p>边际理论取决于对输入扰动的鲁棒性应该导致泛化的直觉，而“最小平坦度”取决于对<i>权重</i>扰动的鲁棒性应该导致泛化的直觉。 </p><figure class="image image_resized" style="width:67.75%"><img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/egfs5to90s8ubnsvkepv" srcset="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/nrxfkdeh4e7m5ab9u1zm 120w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/cogpoyci6z0vkepgbj5d 240w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/mbgxkymhnbuz1usnra0k 360w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/fvooafvib6r1adueusze 480w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/eniulqfgsjssk6gsyjlg 600w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/ffnpzztuby6dkzw2hdbr 720w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/mjvyncg49man3tp0jhwp 840w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/bjbxw2gzxd4ew1gasgc1 960w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/hlzvjeotny6vpquvnved 1080w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/dnb8zu9zsuhogxnuj2no 1155w"><figcaption>更平坦的最小值对于权重扰动更加稳健，因此对于数据扰动也更加稳健。</figcaption></figure><p>如果损失景观的曲率（通过 Hessian 测量）较低，那么权重的微小变化将意味着损失的微小变化。因此，如果我们通过引入新颖的样本（=要求其概括）来扰乱损失情况，我们可能预计损失情况不会发生太大变化。相反，如果曲率较高，则模型会更加复杂并且泛化能力可能较差。</p><p>正如深度学习中的<s>许多</s>想法一样，这可以追溯到<a href="https://proceedings.neurips.cc/paper/1994/file/01882513d5fa7c329e940dda99b12147-Paper.pdf">Hochreiter 和 Schmidhuber 在 90 年代撰写的一篇论文</a>。它们提供了基于算法复杂性理论的最小描述长度 (MDL) 原则的直觉。在 MDL 语言中，需要更少的位来指定“平坦”最小值的位置，并且更简单的函数应该更好地概括。</p><p><a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1609.04836">凯斯卡等人。 (2017)</a>证明小批量 SGD 收敛到更平坦的最小值，并且这与泛化误差密切相关。然而，<a href="https://proceedings.neurips.cc/paper/2017/file/10ce03a1ed01077e3e289f3e53c72813-Paper.pdf">Neyshabur 等人。 (2017a)</a>和<a href="http://proceedings.mlr.press/v70/dinh17b/dinh17b.pdf">Dinh 等人。 (2017)</a>指出这种简单的方法是有缺陷的：锐度可以通过重新参数化任意缩放，并且在随机标签上训练的模型通常比在真实标签上训练的模型具有更平坦的最小值。为了解决这个问题， <a href="http://proceedings.mlr.press/v139/kwon21b/kwon21b.pdf">Kwon 等人。 （2021）</a>提出了<strong>自适应锐度</strong>，它对于重新参数化是不变的，并且似乎与泛化误差密切相关。</p><p>事实证明，自适应清晰度不足以挽救清晰度理论。<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2302.07011">安德留申科等人。 （2023）</a>发现，与经典直觉相反，锐度——甚至是更聪明的重参数化不变概念——与更大数据集上的 Transformer 的泛化关系很差甚至<i>呈负</i>相关。用他们的话来说，“在现代环境中，清晰度<i>并不是</i>概括性的良好指标。”</p><p>还有一个更根本的问题：<a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/6g8cAftfQufLmFDYT/you-re-measuring-model-complexity-wrong">神经网络是奇异的，因此用抛物面局部建模损失景观是无效的</a>。研究对权重变化的敏感性需要更先进的代数几何工具。</p><h3>算法稳定性和鲁棒性</h3><p>对噪声敏感度的另一个概念是最终模型对训练集变化的敏感度。这就是<a href="https://proceedings.neurips.cc/paper/2000/file/49ad23d1ec9fa4bd8d77d02681df5cfa-Paper.pdf">Bousquet 和 Elisseeff (2000)</a><strong>算法稳定性</strong>背后的想法：如果改变训练样本不会改变模型的性能，那么经验风险应该具有较低的方差。</p><p>学习算法被认为具有<strong>一致稳定性</strong><span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="\beta"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.446em; padding-right: 0.007em;">β</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>如果</p><span><span class="mjpage mjpage__block"><span class="mjx-chtml MJXc-display" style="text-align: center;"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="\max _i\left\{\left|\ell\left(f_{w(D_n)}(x_i), y_i\right)-\ell\left(f_{w\left(D_n^{\backslash i}\right)}(x_i), y_i\right)\right|\right\} \leq \beta."><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-munderover"><span class="mjx-itable"><span class="mjx-row"><span class="mjx-cell"><span class="mjx-op"><span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.151em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">max</span></span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-row"><span class="mjx-under" style="font-size: 70.7%; padding-top: 0.236em; padding-bottom: 0.141em; padding-left: 1.143em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">i</span></span></span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mrow MJXc-space1"><span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-size3-R" style="padding-top: 1.256em; padding-bottom: 1.256em;">{</span></span> <span class="mjx-mrow"><span class="mjx-mo" style="vertical-align: -0.718em;"><span class="mjx-delim-v"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">∣</span> <span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="line-height: 0.486em; margin-bottom: 0.014em; margin-top: -0.114em;">∣</span> <span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">∣</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">ℓ</span></span> <span class="mjx-mrow MJXc-space1"><span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-size1-R" style="padding-top: 0.593em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">(</span></span> <span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base" style="margin-right: -0.06em;"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.519em; padding-right: 0.06em;">f</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.275em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-texatom" style=""><span class="mjx-mrow"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">w</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">(</span></span> <span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">D</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 83.3%; vertical-align: -0.18em; padding-right: 0.06em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">n</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">)</span></span></span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">(</span></span> <span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225e