<span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">n</span></span> <span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.446em; padding-right: 0.007em;">β</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo MJXc-space2"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.298em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">+</span></span> <span class="mjx-mn MJXc-space2"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">1</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">)</span></span> <span class="mjx-msqrt"><span class="mjx-box" style="padding-top: 0.045em;"><span class="mjx-surd"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-size4-R" style="padding-top: 1.551em; padding-bottom: 1.551em;">√</span></span> <span class="mjx-box" style="padding-top: 0.044em; border-top: 1px solid;"><span class="mjx-mrow"><span class="mjx-mfrac"><span class="mjx-box MJXc-stacked" style="width: 2.38em; padding: 0px 0.12em;"><span class="mjx-numerator" style="width: 2.38em; top: -2.024em;"><span class="mjx-mrow"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.519em;">log</span></span><span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char"></span></span> <span class="mjx-mfrac MJXc-space1"><span class="mjx-box MJXc-stacked" style="width: 0.495em; padding: 0px 0.12em;"><span class="mjx-numerator" style="font-size: 70.7%; width: 0.7em; top: -1.372em;"><span class="mjx-mn" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">1δ</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-denominator" style="font-size: 70.7%; width: 0.7em; bottom: -0.726em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.007em;">_</span></span></span><span style="border-bottom: 1.3px solid; top: -0.296em; width: 0.495em;" class="mjx-line"></span></span><span style="height: 1.484em; vertical-align: -0.514em;" class="mjx-vsize"></span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-denominator" style="width: 2.38em; bottom: -0.767em;"><span class="mjx-mrow"><span class="mjx-mn"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">2n</span></span> <span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">_</span></span></span></span><span style="border-bottom: 1.3px solid; top: -0.296em; width: 2.38em;" class="mjx-line"></span></span><span style="height: 2.791em; vertical-align: -0.767em;" class="mjx-vsize"></span></span></span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="margin-top: -0.144em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">。</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><p>这种研究途径与<strong>影响函数的</strong>研究（例如， <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2308.03296">Grosse 等人，2023</a> ）以及从<a href="https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/11681878_14">Dwork 等人</a>开始的<strong>差分隐私</strong>研究有很强的相似之处。 <a href="https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/11681878_14">(2006)</a> ，这是为了确保您无法判断样本是否属于训练集。 <a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar?q=Xu%20and%20Mannor%20%282012%29">Xu 和 Mannor (2012)</a>也将其扩展到<strong>算法稳健性</strong>，该算法着眼于更改整个数据集而不是单个示例的敏感性。</p><p>这越来越接近我们已经通过 PAC-Bayes 数据依赖先验看到的观点，其中模型复杂性与模型如何响应附加数据而变化有关。我们将在 SLT 中再次看到这一观点。</p><h2>模型子类复杂性</h2><p>到目前为止，我们已经将泛化视为关于模型类的表达性的问题（它能够如何很好地适应随机噪声），并且我们已经将泛化视为关于特定模型的鲁棒性的问题（它们能够“抵抗”小样本的能力如何）。噪声量）。另一种可能性是将泛化视为有关学习<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="p(w|D_n)"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">模型</span></span><span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">p</span></span> <span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">(</span></span> <span class="mjx-texatom"><span class="mjx-mrow"><span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">w</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">|</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">Dn</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><i>分布</i>的稳健性的问题。</p><p>在本节中，我们将探讨各种复杂性度量，包括检查学习机器的分布如何变化，特别是响应新数据时的变化。我们将在下一节中看到，这将研究泛化变成了比较权重<i>子类</i>的问题。</p><h3>信息论度量</h3><p>现代深度学习理论中研究泛化的更有原则性的方法之一来自一系列与现代 PAC-贝叶斯理论并行（且独立）发展的信息论复杂性度量。在这些界限中显示的复杂性度量是根据权重和数据的各种分布的信息论度量。相关的界限是对权重的期望——不统一。</p><p>我们已经看到了一个关于权重和数据之间的互信息的例子， <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="I(w\, \|\, D_n)"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.064em;">I</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">(</span></span> <span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">w</span></span><span class="mjx-mspace" style="width: 0.167em; height: 0px;"></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">∥</span></span><span class="mjx-mspace" style="width: 0.167em; height: 0px;"></span> <span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">D</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">n</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> ，这是联合分布与边际分布乘积之间的 Kullback-Leibler 散度，</p> <span><span class="mjpage mjpage__block"><span class="mjx-chtml MJXc-display" style="text-align: center;"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="I(w\,\|\, D_n) = D_\mathrm{KL}(p(w,D_n)\,\|\,p(w)\,q(D_n))."><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.064em;">我</span></span><span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">（</span></span> <span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">w</span></span><span class="mjx-mspace" style="width: 0.167em; height: 0px;"></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">∥</span></span><span class="mjx-mspace" style="width: 0.167em; height: 0px;"></span> <span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">D</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">n</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">)</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo MJXc-space3"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.077em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">=</span></span> <span class="mjx-msubsup MJXc-space3"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">D</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-texatom" style=""><span class="mjx-mrow"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">KL</span></span> <span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">(</span></span></span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">p</span></span> <span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">(</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">w</span></span> <span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">,</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="margin-top: -0.144em; padding-bottom: 0.519em;">D</span></span> <span class="mjx-msubsup MJXc-space1"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">n</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">)</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">_</span></span><span class="mjx-mspace" style="width: 0.167em; height: 0px;"></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">∥</span></span><span class="mjx-mspace" style="width: 0.167em; height: 0px;"></span> <span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">p</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">(</span></span> <span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">w</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">)</span></span><span class="mjx-mspace" style="width: 0.167em; height: 0px;"></span> <span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.446em; padding-right: 0.014em;">q</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">(</span></span> <span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">Dn</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">)</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">)</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">。</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="margin-top: -0.144em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">_</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><p>这可能是迄今为止最直观的复杂性概念：如果模型包含有关数据集的更多信息，则模型会更复杂。</p><p>我们在 PAC-Bayes 示例中看到了后验<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="D_\mathrm{KL}(p\|\varphi)"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">D</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-texatom" style=""><span class="mjx-mrow"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">K</span></span> <span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">L</span></span></span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">(</span></span> <span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">p</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">∥</span></span> <span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.519em;">φ</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>之间的 KL 散度的另一个例子。如果模型的权重“更接近”其初始值，则模型“更简单”。</p><p>涉及这些 KL 散度的许多界限可以概括为其他散度，例如更广泛的<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/F-divergence">f 散度</a>族、 <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/R%C3%A9nyi_entropy#R%C3%A9nyi_divergence">Rényi 散度</a>、 <a href="https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/abstract/document/9162168">（条件）最大泄漏</a>、 <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wasserstein_distance">Wasserstein 度量</a>等。还有更多技巧可以挤出到处都有一些额外的概括。</p><p>不幸的是，当将这些界限应用于现实世界的系统时，它们会遇到问题，因为这些信息论指标通常难以计算甚至估计。</p><h3>压缩性</h3><p>基于压缩的边界建立在对权重变化的鲁棒性的最小平坦度/锐度背后的相同想法之上。如果模型具有高度可压缩性，并且您可以在不影响性能的情况下丢弃许多权重，则模型的有效维度低于其表观维度。它比看起来更简单，因此应该进行概括。</p><p><a href="http://proceedings.mlr.press/v80/arora18b/arora18b.pdf">阿罗拉等人。 （2018）</a>提供了开创性的治疗。他们将给定的模型转换为一组更简单的压缩模型，这使他们能够将典型模型类复杂性界限的工具应用于该系列。该框架并不直接预测原始模型的泛化，而是预测构建的子类的泛化。</p><p>周等人。 (2019) 将这个想法与 PAC-Bayes 理论中出现的数据相关先验的想法结合起来。后验被选择为以学习权重为中心的高斯分布，先验被选择为压缩权重的集合（通过修剪获得）。与 Dziugaite 和 Roy (2017) 采取的方法类似，他们通过在非零权重上叠加高斯噪声来添加一点最小锐度。由此产生的边界是神经网络中第一个非空边界，但它们仍然远非严格。</p><p>这种方法的主要限制似乎是这些子类目前是以相当特别的方式构建的。例如，奇异后验不是渐近高斯分布的，因此将后验建模为高斯分布是没有根据的。此外，神经网络还有更多种类的简并性，而不仅仅是可以修剪的权重（例如参见<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1906.00904">Hanin 和 Rolnick 2019</a> ）。这意味着当前的界限可能严重低估了神经网络的实际可压缩性。 </p><figure class="image image_resized" style="width:80.34%"><img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/hr6ene9rmv9elbejf7m1" srcset="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/iuwhmgfd01ixcevxxrsq 410w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/p7hs43lr3ypdlkjcmfib 820w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/qzgvzh7zfiniehyj10qm 1230w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/jcnsckxb9gkbevuaiohe 1640w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/vorkcaxkcjjuic1vb0ir 2050w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/x7ahiwhdukjjqzylmf4o 2460w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/ikulw2ffhd8qi7cnhzg8 2870w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/bxllmjixejuv1x55fnvo 3280w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/p8rrhmuvlbnnk6c7jwzd 3690w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/jzkpauic5nhmxpo4dnba 4070w"><figcaption>学习权重的分布并不渐近于正态分布，因此涉及构建权重的人工高斯分布的基于压缩的边界是不合理的。</figcaption></figure><p> SLT 的学习系数是更自然的可压缩性概念的一个竞争者。尽管与最小描述长度 (MDL) 原则和可压缩性等想法的确切联系是一个悬而未决的问题，但很明显，学习系数捕获了更丰富的简并性，例如，可以修剪的权重数量。</p><h3>自由能/随机复杂度</h3><p>给定似然度和先验，我们可以将贝叶斯<strong>自由能（</strong>或<strong>随机复杂度）</strong> <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="F_n"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base" style="margin-right: -0.106em;"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.106em;">F</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">n</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>定义为<strong>边际似然度</strong>（或<strong>模型证据</strong>）的负对数：</p> <span><span class="mjpage mjpage__block"><span class="mjx-chtml MJXc-display" style="text-align: center;"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="\begin{align}F_n&amp;=-\log p(D_n),\\&amp;=-\log \int_\mathcal W p(w|D_n)\,\varphi(w)\,\mathrm d w,\\&amp;=-\log\int_\mathcal w e^{-nL_n(w)}\,\varphi(w)\,\mathrm dw,\end{align}"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mtable" style="vertical-align: -2.935em; padding: 0px 0.167em;"><span class="mjx-table"><span class="mjx-mtr" style="heigh