X-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">w</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-stack" style="vertical-align: -0.157em;"><span class="mjx-sup" style="font-size: 70.7%; padding-bottom: 0.255em; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mo" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.151em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">∗</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">α</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>是<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="W_\alpha"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base" style="margin-right: -0.104em;"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.104em;">W</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">α</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>内<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="L_n"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">L</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">n</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>的最小值，并且<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="\lambda_\alpha"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">λ</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">α</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>是与具有相关重数<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="m_\alpha"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">m</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">α</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>的最小值集合相关联的最大<i>局部</i>RLCT。</p><p>尽管自由能（局部或全局）与权重空间的密集区域相关，但其极限形式由这些区域内非常特殊的权重的零测度子集主导——不仅仅是<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="W_\alpha"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base" style="margin-right: -0.104em;"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.104em;">W</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">α</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>内的最小值集合，还包括这些最小值内最奇点的集合。无论您选择什么粗粒度<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="W_\alpha"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base" style="margin-right: -0.104em;"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.104em;">W</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">α</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> ，子类的性能以及它们之间的选择过程都将由与这些奇点相关的一组原则性可观察值的值主导：学习系数、奇异波动和多重性。</p><p> SLT 可观测量不仅从理论中更自然地出现，而且它们本质上<i>是非局部的</i>。给定一个任意选择权重的模型，当您继续抽取更多样本时，该点概率密度的变化将由附近奇点集主导。因此，您不能纯粹根据单个权重的行为来理解泛化。同样，你不能纯粹从全球角度理解泛化。根据所涉及的“时间尺度”（您绘制的样本数量），不同的奇点将主导学习过程，从而主导泛化。子类是自然的研究单位。</p><h2>为什么神经网络具有泛化能力</h2><p>对于常规模型，学习系数和多重性是恒定的，因此内部模型选择的过程通常简化为简单地寻找使损失最小化的子类。对于奇异模型，该过程非常不同：学习系数和多重性可能会有所不同，因此最小化自由能需要权衡准确性与复杂性，而复杂性取决于当前样本的数量。</p><p>让我们只关注前两个术语：</p> <span><span class="mjpage mjpage__block"><span class="mjx-chtml MJXc-display" style="text-align: center;"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="F_n(W_\alpha) \approx nL_n(w_\alpha^*) + \lambda_\alpha \log n."><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base" style="margin-right: -0.106em;"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.106em;">F</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">n</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">(</span></span> <span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base" style="margin-right: -0.104em;"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.104em;">W</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">α</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">)</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo MJXc-space3"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">≈</span></span> <span class="mjx-mi MJXc-space3"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">n</span></span> <span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">L</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">n</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">(</span></span> <span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">w</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-stack" style="vertical-align: -0.157em;"><span class="mjx-sup" style="font-size: 70.7%; padding-bottom: 0.255em; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mo" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.151em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">*</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">α</span></span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">)</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo MJXc-space2"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.298em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">+</span></span> <span class="mjx-msubsup MJXc-space2"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">λ</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">α</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mi MJXc-space1"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.519em;">log</span></span><span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char"></span></span> <span class="mjx-mi MJXc-space1"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">名词</span></span><span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="margin-top: -0.144em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">_</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><p>要在给定<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="n"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">n</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>的不同子模型上最小化此公式，您可以降低损失<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="L_n"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">L</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">n</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>或复杂度<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="\lambda_\alpha"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">λ</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">α</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> 。这是奥卡姆剃刀在准确性和复杂性之间进行权衡的又一体现。与其他形式不同，内部模型选择意味着单一贝叶斯学习器<i>自动</i>执行这种权衡。</p><p>当你改变<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="n"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">n</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>时会发生什么？随着<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="n"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">n</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>的增加，精度和复杂性之间的权衡将越来越倾向于线性精度项而不是对数复杂性项。因此，模型将变得更加准确，但代价是增加了复杂性——通过查看更多样本获得的附加信息可以保证这一成本。这使得奇异模型在整个学习过程中保持记忆和泛化之间的最佳权衡。</p><p>这种自动权衡解释了为什么像神经网络这样的单一学习机器能够在实践中进行泛化。但它并没有解释为什么低损耗解决方案集应该包含任何具有低 RLCT 的点的相关问题。 <a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/gq9GR6duzcuxyxZtD/approximation-is-expensive-but-the-lunch-is-cheap">正如上一篇文章中所讨论的</a>，这似乎需要更深入地了解哪些类型的数据是“自然的”以及神经网络架构的特殊之处。仍然存在一些谜团。</p><h2>神经网络如何泛化</h2><p>我们不仅仅对学习机器能够泛化的<i>原因</i>感兴趣。我们感兴趣的是<i>如何</i>。神经网络将采用哪些特定的泛化策略？</p><p>有大量工作研究神经网络的“归纳偏差”，但这些文献仍处于早期阶段。结果是高度经验性的，缺乏泛化界限研究背后的统一数学形式主义。 <span class="footnote-reference" role="doc-noteref" id="fnrefd4mw3ckys99"><sup><a href="#fnd4mw3ckys99">[7]</a></sup></span>我们能做得更好吗？研究学习机归纳偏差的正确数学形式是什么？</p><p> SLT 提供了一些提示。学习系数告诉我们泛化与后验/自由能<i>变化</i>之间的深层联系。这将泛化和优化置于同一基础上，这是我们在其他一些地方看到的链接：依赖于数据的先验（其中界限涉及不同数据选择下学习机之间的位数）、算法稳定性/鲁棒性（其中界限是模型响应额外样本而变化的程度），以及涉及权重和数据之间的相互信息的界限。</p><p>特别是，SLT 讲述了泛化和<i>几何</i>之间的联系，特别是几何的变化。该几何形状来自数据生成过程和模型类的对称性。事后看来，存在这样的联系并不奇怪。对称性决定物理性质的思想是现代理论物理学的基础。为什么学习机会是例外？</p><p>从这个角度来看，自然要问的问题是我们可以从局部几何中提取多少信息。我们可以使用几何来了解神经网络的内部结构吗？特别是，当物理学家谈论<i>结构</i>时，他们指的是相关函数——在学习理论中，这意味着像<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="\mathbb E[w_i w_j]"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-texatom"><span class="mjx-mrow"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-ams-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">E</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">[</span></span> <span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">w</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">i</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">w</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.519em;">j</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">]</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>和<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="\mathbb E[w_i w_j w_k]"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-texatom"><span class="mjx-mrow"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-ams-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">E</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">[</span></span> <span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">w</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">i</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">w</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.519em;">j</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">w</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.219em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">k</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">]</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>这样的张量。代数几何和统计物理学拥有非常复杂的工具来研究这种更精细尺度的几何结构——迄今为止，这些工具一直被学习理论所忽视。</p><p>一旦我们开始研究相关函数，我们就超越了标量热力学领域进入了统计物理学领域。因此，也许我们需要从<i>为什么</i>泛化转向<i>如何</i>泛化，这就是我们学习观点的相应变化：从学习的热力学到学习的统计物理学。</p><h2>未来的研究</h2><p>将更广泛的泛化理论领域引入单一学习理论方面，有很多唾手可得的成果。将 SLT 的结果扭曲为更典型的 (PAC-Bayes) 类型的边界并表明您可以击败当前最先进的泛化边界是一项艰巨的工作。充实了与压缩理论、算法稳定性和裕度理论的联系（例如，均匀稳定性看起来与奇异波动<i>非常</i>相似）。在将 SLT 与信息论泛化理论联系起来方面还有更多有趣的工作，这可能会产生关于 SLT 思想的新视角（例如，基于 MDL 的 SLT 框架）。</p><p>在<a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/nN7bHuHZYaWv9RDJL/announcing-timaeus">Timaeu​​s</a> ，我们目前专注于将统计物理学工具导入学习理论中，以从几何角度研究结构。第一次，数百名物理学家花费了数十年的时间才建立了统计物理学。我们很乐观，这次可以做得更快，但我们需要帮助。<a href="https://devinterp.com/discord">如果您对此感兴趣，请联系</a>。</p><blockquote><p>感谢<a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/users/daniel-murfet?mention=user">@Daniel Murfet</a> 、 <a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/users/edmund-lau?mention=user">@Edmund Lau</a> 、 <a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/users/zach-furman?mention=user">@Zach Furman</a> 、 <a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/users/liam-carroll?mention=user">@Liam Carroll</a> 、 <a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/users/stan-van-wingerden?mention=user">@Stan van Wingerden</a>和<a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/users/alexander-gietelink-oldenziel?mention=user">@Alexander Gietelink Oldenziel</a>对本文的反馈。</p><p>如果您想了解有关泛化理论的更多信息，请查看<a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/2309.04381">Hellström 等人。 （2023）</a> 。 </p></blockquote><ol class="footnotes" role="doc-endnotes"><li class="footnote-item" role="doc-endnote" id="fnmi3y61rzz9d"> <span class="footnote-back-link"><sup><strong><a href="#fnrefmi3y61rzz9d">^</a></strong></sup></span><div class="footnote-content"><p>我将重点关注监督设置，其中我们使用参数化的确定性函数<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="f_w"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-bas